name: Caligo novum - The new owl butterfly
description: "The new Caligo butterflies are adapted to the outer space environment. Their wings figure a bigger animal to confuse predators. Each butterfly has a unique pattern, like a fingerprint, that's why most collectors desire them."  This is a digitally developed art originally painted on its negative colors on paper using watercolor technique. This limited edition of the reveled piece is 4021x3097 px, 6.3 MB, painted in 140lb cold pressed cotton paper (8.6x9 inches).
